div.font: User chooses to login/sign up using PAW.js

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Lato; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 96px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

div.font: User either chooses to login with one of the existing identities or chooses to create a new one via signup.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Lato; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 96px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

div.font: User at this point has either been granted a session to use the web app or not.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Lato; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: bold; text-align: center;
display: inline-block; font-size: 8px; font-family: Lato; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 126px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

div.font: Web app origin JS opens a new Window to the origin hosting/utilizing PAW.js

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Lato; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 126px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;
div.div: Using cross-document messaging, it will initiate the authentication with the PAW.js origin.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Lato; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 96px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

div.font: Web app origin JS will then send this signed message to the web app backend authentication endpoint.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Lato; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: bold; text-align: center;
display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Lato; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 136px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;
div.div:
PAW.js acknowledges the request and displays the origin to the user.
It then attempts to load and display all existing identities stored in the browser's IndexedDB storage for that origin only.
Next, it populates the existing identities for the user to choose for login and/or allows the user to signup with a new identity.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Lato; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 126px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

div.span: PAW.js either cryptographically signs a login request or creates the new identity and signs a new signup request. Sends this signed message back to the web app origin Window. PAW.js origin Window will close.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Lato; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: bold; text-align: center;
display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Lato; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 96px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

div.font: Web app responds with client-side JS and login page.

div.style: display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Lato; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 96px; white-space: normal; word-wrap: normal; text-align: center;

div.font: Web app backend validates the login/signup request and then either grants the user a session or not.
